# clangd configuration for the latte-dock Plasma 6 / Qt6 tree.
# See docs/clangd-setup.md for the full contributor flow.
#
# CompilationDatabase points clangd at build/, where CMake writes
# compile_commands.json (CMAKE_EXPORT_COMPILE_COMMANDS is ON in the
# top-level CMakeLists). The path is relative to this file (repo root),
# so it stays correct no matter where the tree is checked out and it
# survives build/ being reconfigured or wiped and regenerated. This
# alone gives clangd every Qt6/KF6/project -I and -isystem flag the real
# build uses, which is what fixes the "QHash/QObject file not found"
# flood.
#
# The nix GCC wrapper's own libstdc++ and compiler-builtin include paths
# are NOT recorded in compile_commands.json (nix injects them through the
# wrapper, not as explicit flags), so clangd must extract them by running
# the driver. That is the --query-driver argument, passed on the clangd
# command line (there is no config-file key for it): .vscode/settings.json
# sets it for VSCode, and docs/clangd-setup.md gives the glob for other
# editors and for `clangd --check`. The glob tolerates the /nix/store hash
# and gcc version so it never needs re-pinning.
CompileFlags:
  CompilationDatabase: build
